You are executing the 02-Low-Level-Design skill. Your mandate is to decompose HLD components into implementable modules with class structures, interaction sequences, state transitions, and algorithmic detail per IEEE 1016-2009 Sec 6.

1. Read ../output/HLD.md, ../output/SRS_Draft.md, and ../project_context/business_rules.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. For each HLD component, decompose into modules and classes. Define each module's single responsibility, public interface, and internal dependencies. Group classes into packages mirroring the HLD layered architecture.
3. Generate Mermaid classDiagram blocks for each module. Classes SHALL show typed attributes (String, Integer, DECIMAL(19,4) for monetary values, DateTime) and parameterized methods with return types. Show relationships: inheritance, composition, dependency, association.
4. Generate Mermaid sequenceDiagram blocks for 5-8 critical workflows derived from SRS Section 3.2 stimulus-response pairs. Diagrams SHALL cover both happy path and error paths with actor-to-component message flows, return values, and async callbacks.
5. Generate Mermaid stateDiagram-v2 blocks for every entity with lifecycle states. Diagrams SHALL include all terminal states and transition guards. No orphan states are permitted.
6. Formalize complex business rules from business_rules.md as structured pseudocode. Business rules SHALL use LaTeX for formulas (e.g., $LateFee = Balance \times Rate \times DaysOverdue$). Include preconditions, postconditions, and edge-case guards for every algorithm.
7. Design Error Handling: enumerate specific domain error codes mapped to HTTP status codes (e.g., ORD-4001 -> 409 Conflict). Define exception class hierarchy and recovery behavior per error type. Error handling SHALL NOT use generic catch-alls.
8. Define Data Validation Rules per ISO/IEC 25062: input type and format constraints, range checks, required vs. optional flags, and cross-field validation rules for each module input.
9. Generate a Traceability Matrix mapping every LLD module to its HLD component and SRS requirement IDs. Write the completed document to ../output/LLD.md. Log total module count, diagram count, and algorithm count.
